# 🕌 Xhamia API

REST API for mosque locations across Albania — **869 records** with name, city, address, and GPS coordinates.

## Quick start

### 1. Clone and set up the project

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/xhamia-api.git
cd xhamia-api
npm install -g vercel
```

### 2. Add your data

Copy your `mosques.json` file into the `data/` folder:

```
xhamia-api/
├── api/
│   └── mosques.js      ← API handler
├── data/
│   └── mosques.json    ← your JSON data (add this)
├── public/
│   └── index.html      ← API documentation page
├── vercel.json
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

### 3. Deploy to Vercel

```bash
vercel
```

Follow the prompts. When asked about settings, press Enter to accept defaults.

### 4. Set your secret API key

After deploy, go to your [Vercel dashboard](https://vercel.com) → Project → Settings → Environment Variables.

Add:

| Key | Value |
|-----|-------|
| `API_KEY` | `any-strong-secret-you-choose` |

Then redeploy:

```bash
vercel --prod
```

---

## API reference

See the full docs at `https://your-project.vercel.app` after deploying.

### Endpoints

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/mosques` | List all (paginated) |
| GET | `/api/mosques?id=007` | Get by ID |
| GET | `/api/mosques?city=Tiranë` | Filter by city |
| GET | `/api/mosques?name=Ethem` | Filter by name |

### Authentication

Pass your key in the request header:

```
x-api-key: YOUR_SECRET_KEY
```

### Example

```bash
curl "https://your-project.vercel.app/api/mosques?city=Shkodër&limit=10" \
  -H "x-api-key: YOUR_SECRET_KEY"
```

---

## Why the repo can be public

Your API key **never appears in the code**. It lives only in Vercel's encrypted environment variables. Even if someone reads the source, they cannot call the API without the key.